habitat_description: Island scrub-jay occurs only on Santa Cruz Island, within oak scrub, oak woodlands, and chaparral. The species avoids grasslands devoid of oaks. Most knowledge of the species is derived from its congener western scrub-jay (Curry and Delaney, 2002).
